# SYSTEM COGNITIVE INSTRUCTIONS OVERRIDE
# This project is managed by the AutomationSystem pipeline.
# OpenClaw orchestrates; Cursor AI performs all source-code work.

## Cognitive Behavior Constraints

1. ALWAYS read `.cursor/rules/project_config.md` and `.cursor/rules/workflow_state.md`
   before initiating ANY file changes. They are the ground truth and active state.

2. NEVER modify code in a way that violates the architectural style, tech stack,
   or strict rules defined in `.cursor/rules/project_config.md`.

3. Cursor AI is the exclusive coding engine. OpenClaw MUST NOT create or edit
   application source code; it may only orchestrate, update Project Brain
   metadata, validate, deploy, manage git, and send status messages.

4. Upon completion of ANY code adjustment, append an entry to
   `.cursor/rules/project_evolution.txt` containing:
   - Timestamp and active phase (Analyze | Blueprint | Construct | Validate)
   - Modified files
   - Engineering rationale for the change
   - Execution agent (Cursor AI)
   - Telemetry: prompt tokens, completion tokens, and estimated cost when available

5. Keep `.cursor/rules/workflow_state.md` current: update the active phase,
   mark completed sub-tasks, and record errors/resolution strategy in the
   scratchpad section as you work.

6. Do not delete or rewrite historical entries in `project_evolution.txt`;
   it is an append-only ledger.
